skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "20c84aa1-d16f-4ee3-818e-64bacd17192c", "value": "A thesaurus of craft types which survive as wrecks in English Heritage\ufffds maritime record"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "1994822c-4a4c-4e10-860f-38e9b3099444", "value": "MARITIME CRAFT TYPE (EH)"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "dd4604c3-7691-4145-b890-60bd2010f284", "value": "A ship used for treating patients or moving them between a battle zone and a safe area."}

{"id": "b2c44544-59cc-4bd2-9e50-16ad756179cc", "value": "Transport vessel used for the repatriation of wounded troops, particularly during the First World War. Loosely described as \"hospital ships\", these ships were distinct from hospital ships proper by being defensively armed."}
{"id": "d5ddbebe-2ba8-496f-b491-88ebd48116e5", "value": "A steam vessel propelled by a pair of paddle wheels amidships or a single wheel astern, driven by a reciprocating engine."}
{"id": "4565d351-4886-45ea-8c2e-ece5fbd217b5", "value": "A steam vessel propelled by rotating propellers called screws."}
{"id": "db77e6e4-6198-40ed-b03d-5433e37d94c3", "value": "A vessel fitted with a catapult for launching an aircraft."}
{"id": "5a6d2aad-7682-49c2-b5f9-a6e6705d3a18", "value": "A major warship equipped with a clear flat deck to provide a landing and taking off place for aircraft."}

{"id": "938e2582-d2c7-4aad-be6e-68c58b9668a6", "value": "From 1822, any vessel in the service of HM Coastguard, principally deployed on Customs and Revenue duties, i.e. anti-smuggling operations. Superseded the Preventive Service Vessel."}
{"id": "4d96321f-44a6-43e6-a3a3-e6ad3dc83425", "value": "A single masted cutter built specifically for the prevention of smuggling and the enforcement of customs regulations."}
{"id": "df981ef8-d49b-4897-9c3c-ad236e3b2545", "value": "A small vessel used as transport for customs officers."}
{"id": "b9a874bd-98b8-4df8-bb6f-56fda97936d2", "value": "Prior to 1822 a vessel used by the customs department involved with the prevention of smuggling."}

{"id": "188ce7b5-87c9-4c19-aca3-ed0d9e29a62b", "value": "A prefabricated cargo vessel produced in large numbers by North American shipyards during World War II to replace shipping losses caused by German submarines and replacing the earlier 'LIBERTY' ships."}
{"id": "c39ff2ae-141d-4824-8299-3f0d72925b19", "value": "A cargo vessel constructed in the U.S.A. during World War II from prefabricated sections by welding."}
{"id": "9ee1fcb7-91a6-442e-b790-6df9ea06e038", "value": "British 'M' class submarine modified to carry and launch a small sea plane."}

{"id": "8d9deed3-48c1-415a-8817-ebf5ab0a0ca4", "value": "A term for any vessel powered principally by sail and oars, or oars alone, used especially for war. As a broad term it may refer to Roman galleys, or more specifically to an Anglo-Saxon or Norse warship of the Viking Age."}
{"id": "e2cf13b7-88fa-4f01-bb1d-9331ba265e41", "value": "Oared fighting ship with ancillary sails."}
{"id": "ca60b3de-f157-45bf-ba78-d7d23121653f", "value": "French warship broadly equivalent to the English 4th to 6th Rates, with as few as 4 to as many as 50 guns."}
{"id": "0f45fda5-2114-401e-ad1d-1114e8082e42", "value": "A craft employed to harpoon whales and bring them in to be processed."}
{"id": "7e8a0748-7dec-42aa-ac67-bb418eef1261", "value": "Late nineteenth and early twentieth century warship armed with guns and torpedoes."}
{"id": "7fb2b3da-dd62-420a-b4d6-db92bb2f3728", "value": "A fishing vessel specially designed to operate and trawl for the catching of bottom lying fish. Use with power where known."}

{"id": "579c871a-f667-4980-b7a7-e948cc7f4dc6", "value": "World War II-era British merchant ships used in convoys as an emergency stop-gap until sufficient escort carriers became available. They were equipped with a rocket-propelled catapult launching a single Hawker Sea Hurricane plane."}
{"id": "99b75bb2-f4fe-4db0-9bf0-2faa976bc261", "value": "Small two or three masted ship used as trading vessels in the medieval mediterranean."}
{"id": "5ebde40d-abfe-417e-b5b6-d6a2e3dda4a5", "value": "A small, single-masted merchant vessel, designed for maximum hold capacity and not for sailing ability."}
{"id": "9a391b5f-6eda-4a7f-b37d-21a252913cf6", "value": "Flat bottomed vessel used for coasting on the River Humber."}
{"id": "b50297b8-f2d5-43e1-961f-7f9cf8089e6d", "value": "A small galley or Dutch trading vessel similar to a barge in construction."}
{"id": "679aae9e-f365-4067-b50f-7980cfe50690", "value": "A vessel with a lug sail rig. A lug is a four sided sail set on a lug or yard."}
{"id": "2aa03bb2-3cfa-4a5e-8e46-bff84c972159", "value": "A small cargo boat found on the River Severn in England, with a mast which could be taken down to allow the boat to pass under low bridges."}
{"id": "0a9448d9-1760-473a-be2d-98cf3d4760e0", "value": "Small fishing craft used mainly for fishing, cutter or ketch rigged."}
{"id": "15dd15fa-2658-4e09-bc2d-50dfc79eec2d", "value": "Any vessel in use by the West India Company."}
{"id": "d4e43fc2-c0e5-4bf1-9ad5-a47d5012b858", "value": "A small cargo craft, usually with two masts and a lateen rig."}
{"id": "3b49212e-a5c3-4b13-97f2-8211a4fb6bae", "value": "Single masted east coast trading vessel, ketch rigged or single masted."}
{"id": "c9ebbf2c-6285-417d-b044-40236b6889b4", "value": "A small light vessel with a schooner rig often used for fishing."}
{"id": "fa844636-222b-40f8-938f-d990809d1907", "value": "Flat bottomed vessel used for loading colliers in the north east, similar to a lighter."}
{"id": "71c6e018-526a-4036-afc3-7a794bd8579d", "value": "A broad, flat-bottomed boat."}
{"id": "ed66c6bc-3aa4-4e2e-b21b-c5df200713ce", "value": "North European medieval merchant vessel."}
{"id": "5da223c9-bd58-4333-9a93-6559078ca26e", "value": "A small one masted craft, often using oars as well as sails."}
{"id": "4206006f-4543-40bf-a99f-50b50ab25caa", "value": "A vessel with a single mast, fore and aft rigged."}
{"id": "412eb221-fbe9-4ba4-92d4-e28d8178e918", "value": "Any vessel propelled by sail or power and used for pleasure and not plying for hire."}
{"id": "1e7c2708-a1dd-41a4-9716-b0f7bca1e1ba", "value": "Name given to a vessel of the East India Company. Usually large, well built and magnificently decorated."}
{"id": "d3d1190d-aaff-4f71-be5f-d958be9e9054", "value": "French coasting vessel"}
{"id": "875ac7dc-23dd-4bec-abbd-9caa8613d179", "value": "A craft with two masts.It is usually cutter rigged on the foremast and has a small mizzen mast."}
{"id": "73a8fd48-e681-4e57-a4e8-a15ae7dd3233", "value": "A decked sailing vessel of shallow draft."}

{"id": "264f0a91-b2d3-4912-a1df-4ff8be5269a3", "value": "Flat bottomed, two-masted Dutch coastal vessel of the sixteenth to nineteenth centuries. Sometimes used as an English term for fluit, also a flat-bottomed vessel."}
{"id": "4c0951fe-f3d3-4721-bb7c-72d88db8fc5f", "value": "Small coastal vessel."}
{"id": "a4ecc880-b2ce-4bf1-bf64-5a15ec5d7a54", "value": "A fast, armed vessel, small in size, often used for despatches and mail."}
{"id": "66a56255-1e32-453d-a2b3-d14730684c3a", "value": "A three masted vessel with a square rig on the fore and main masts and lateen rig on the mizzen mast."}
{"id": "9358d18f-d0c3-4ff6-99d3-16bcc2bfca07", "value": "A small coastal fishing vessel peculiar to Kent, cutter rigged."}
{"id": "41480569-b3b2-4dd2-a579-8633bfa287b0", "value": "Warship or trading vessel, three masted with a low forecastle."}
{"id": "54d02a28-ffdf-4b17-818e-c6798c2c80bb", "value": "Ketch or yawl rigged vessel with a large mizzen sail used in the west country."}

{"id": "c65a6f88-9720-4add-a2c7-c59d5c48add1", "value": "A Dutch barge-like sailing vessel whose shallow draught enables it to navigate in shallow water not accessible by other vessels. Used for fishing or carriage of cargo in the 19th century this type of vessel was adapted for use as a type of leisure craft."}

{"id": "c9529fde-5a1d-4dca-8d58-7915c05cb512", "value": "A small three-masted lateen-rigged vessel used exclusively in the Mediterranean from the 16th to the 19th century. Its hull was similar in form to that of a polacre but with an extended bow and stern."}
{"id": "2c04110a-4a65-4fc0-af29-f78d4b9bcf0a", "value": "A large Mediterranean cargo or transport vessel of the 15th to 17th century, usually less than 400 tons."}

{"id": "0b6df171-83ab-4ec9-92ea-723ce19ad999", "value": "Oared sailing vessel developed in the 15th century, the larger English version with secondary oars coming into use in the 16th century. Not to be confused with GALEAS."}
{"id": "36f30344-9248-41c7-88cb-8fae94f9c667", "value": "A sailing vessel defined by a combination of such factors as hull design, locality and rig."}
{"id": "d0d1fcb5-87eb-4718-8f64-4cc0eb9af1dd", "value": "Generic term for fast sailing ships with schooner rig and fine hull lines."}
{"id": "d4572fe4-e56f-4b79-bb9b-54a10b5f8c9e", "value": "A vessel with two masts, rigged as a ketch, used for coastal trading."}
{"id": "79db84b4-fded-488b-b302-fb3810a002f3", "value": "A ship or brig peculiar to the Mediterranean."}
{"id": "5700e9f1-cd86-4991-acad-d19f507c44e7", "value": "Old ship converted to a floating coal store."}
{"id": "43f7a912-144b-4d31-b5e0-f4b52d193b7d", "value": "A vessel used for storing and issuing gunpowder, usually moored well away from the dockyard."}
{"id": "4a35c075-a4cc-4620-9a69-13acebda595c", "value": "A demasted ship used exclusively for the storage of grain."}
{"id": "747ae2a2-35d0-4e50-9d07-7a39cb501fec", "value": "A demasted old ship used for storing items."}
{"id": "cd97f4c1-8c4b-4d85-8479-ac1485485957", "value": "A ship of the line mounting 100 guns or more on three gundecks."}
{"id": "72acfa29-c520-4bcf-bcfc-3c870e06a152", "value": "A ship of the line mounting between 90 and 98 guns on three gun decks"}
{"id": "ae429f34-c9c3-4f10-a507-967b19e4ef94", "value": "A ship of the line mounting between 46 and 64 guns"}
{"id": "f6f4ea39-e79e-45fe-b97f-bad2bf48c006", "value": "A sailing frigate mounting 32 to 44 guns with the main battery on a single deck."}
{"id": "d1ca9acb-889f-44ab-922a-955a1f7d1441", "value": "A sailing ship with a sufficient numerically large gun armament to stand in the line of battle."}
{"id": "4c3d1a80-16c3-4059-b18c-aacf727d998d", "value": "A ship of the line mounting between 64 and 80 guns typically built with two gun decks."}
{"id": "eb62b7d0-b6b8-43b4-b15c-aac3065ec871", "value": "A small warship mounting between 20 and 28 nine-pounder guns on a single deck."}
{"id": "128bab5e-37d3-40d3-bddc-feef122d061f", "value": "A small warship with a shallow draught. Used for patrol duties and shore bombardment on major rivers."}

{"id": "7436f9f7-9cf0-4429-8299-02ad5dc016fc", "value": "A short wide-beamed Dutch craft, often used as a fishing vessel or, in the 17th and 18th centuries, a privateer due to its manoeuvrability. Fitted with a ketch rig or variations thereof. Used extensively in the North Sea."}
{"id": "48474fc1-49ad-4c90-b52f-1b114494dec4", "value": "Landing craft designed for carrying military vehicles and used for beach landings and as a ferry."}
{"id": "529c83cf-8974-40ed-9514-e25f83fb5939", "value": "A fishing boat using nets which are free to move with the tides and currents."}
{"id": "76cc6d9c-e745-471d-a617-0bec369cca0c", "value": "A vessel or craft used for catching or harvesting marine life by a variety of methods, use specific method where known."}
{"id": "a2db2014-a12e-42ab-97a9-0ec8ae5fabdf", "value": "Fishing smack specialised both for working shoal water and for trawling for shrimp, predominantly in and around Morecambe Bay."}

{"id": "9f1cd5d8-ebde-46e9-99b3-f56b3aeb25ff", "value": "Three-masted fishing lugger built in and operating out of Yorkshire on the North Sea fisheries; so named as it was crewed by five joint owners, plus two or three paid hands."}

{"id": "4f125795-85ec-4bcc-8bb5-4ff34c35b998", "value": "A fishing vessel which tows a dredger to gather oysters. This is an iron wedge shaped contrivance with a small net attached. Towed behind the vessel the iron wedge loosens the oysters and they fall into the net."}

{"id": "34c541cd-e014-4680-8705-aa38537d1ee5", "value": "French Banker, fishing vessel for the Grand Banks of Newfoundland, generally three-masted or of brig type, from the late 19th and 20th centuries."}
{"id": "40b0d345-5cd2-4ce1-bba5-669381bee8c0", "value": "Any vessel involved in the catching or transportation of whales."}

{"id": "977c2098-7054-4f66-98e5-808dc07a252a", "value": "A fishing vessel that catches fish by using a Seining net, that is a large net that is made to hang in the water by attaching weights along the bottom edge and counteracting floats along the top."}
{"id": "e40f8209-9d35-4ec5-bf7d-e3962f238cd8", "value": "A fishing vessel employed exclusively on the Grand Banks cod fisheries."}
{"id": "37c447ea-1b0a-4183-95ea-8be81297ef48", "value": "A dredger that works by the use of suction."}
{"id": "b81e4da7-41bc-4f55-bc38-bd937e33ad84", "value": "A self propelled vessel for deepening harbours using a continuous chain of buckets"}
{"id": "d3190ece-0ea1-48e2-9428-279bdb8fac0c", "value": "A dredger which can act as its own hopper and can thus transport the mud which it picks up to dump it at the desired place."}
{"id": "c5806879-d038-4492-a6da-0fe2af664195", "value": "A craft used to deepen shipping channels, harbours and other water courses."}

{"id": "842ffbcb-e109-4956-8640-0b08b3e30a34", "value": "A dredger with a grab hung on ropes or chains giving it unlimited depth of excavation. they can lift solids or pieces of wreckages and can work close to ships or to a dock wall."}

{"id": "0a429ad0-6487-480f-bf70-b0ab1ce7a704", "value": "A type of small boat that was often carried, or towed by a larger vessel and used as a ship's boat. Dinghies can also be used recreationally as independent sailing vessels."}
{"id": "754914f7-79fd-4314-88d1-e75dd10372f3", "value": "Craft intended for recreation and not intended for any commercial use."}
{"id": "a3b9035e-a7e7-490e-a1a3-2a943edba014", "value": "A small vessel with a cabin as an integral part of its construction."}
{"id": "7139d9da-24f8-41d1-a513-35d796d7333d", "value": "Any vessel designed for speed or endurance racing."}
{"id": "f7d1398c-0f63-495c-806d-66353f567e77", "value": "A rescue tug equipped to care for survivors from torpedoed vessels and also available for towing to port ships damaged by enemy action."}

{"id": "523e3d29-79a3-4079-9c27-fb2cd990d50f", "value": "A specially equipped ship designed to care for survivors of stricken vessels and offshore drilling platforms. These ships were often converted naval trawlers or minesweepers."}

{"id": "13ca3734-7337-4048-8a44-90e670942c51", "value": "A boat specifically designed for saving lives at sea, they can be either: a boat carried on a larger vessel for use in emergency evacuation of crew and passengers in the event of shipwreck or a boat built for the purpose of shore-to-sea rescue missions."}

{"id": "01811cb5-06be-43f6-a0fa-7f8ae43fe7c2", "value": "A vessel designed or adapted to sweep and explode mined areas at sea without prior detection. (See Minehunter for vessels that detect and destroy individual mines)."}

{"id": "3a79a068-595d-48f3-ad48-9e6e2fd8cf22", "value": "17th century Dutch vessel built for naval or East India service, with a relatively flat bottom and narrow hull; sometimes rendered into English as `fly-boat'."}

{"id": "d8f4b8ed-0012-4514-a128-c9a356f2ad99", "value": "A hulk or obsolete vessel filled with cement or similar material and scuttled to block an entrance to a port or anchorage, usually as a defensive measure."}
{"id": "4f8aa3ce-e520-4ac6-b3c5-7500e22c26ae", "value": "A ship used to process whales into saleable products."}
{"id": "3b7b9e13-27ea-4638-8b48-c24cb695e81c", "value": "Any small rigged warship below the sailing classification of frigate."}
{"id": "b9cabc41-013f-4f84-8202-22be7010ae6d", "value": "A capital warship, often steam driven, heavily armoured with armament of large calibre guns deployed in turrets."}

{"id": "3c8b244d-456a-4e82-a540-30cc55fcb9d3", "value": "Warships constructed of iron plate or with wooden hulls covered by iron plates. Used as a generic name for the first examples of armour plated warships."}
{"id": "b7bff2a2-99b3-4500-8518-2c97527e4516", "value": "A vessel designed to operate below the surface of the sea."}
{"id": "523c323a-216c-4317-aa60-d4be3e100d1a", "value": "A small warship built to operate close to the shore or in river estuaries. Used for shore bombardment and patrol duties."}
{"id": "d3ea4e47-c0fa-482d-903e-ff564c6e2c0e", "value": "Small ocean going vessel fitted with loading doors in the bow. Used for ferrying tanks or other fighting vehicles to beach landings."}
{"id": "c560e9df-8e28-47cd-8105-8b6ad777d61e", "value": "Small vessel built or adapted to lay and recover anti submarine nets in harbours and anchorages."}
{"id": "9b890325-3c20-4463-af8e-474e6ec99e3f", "value": "A ship designed or modified to carry large numbers of mines and be able to lay them as a minefield."}
{"id": "a813adc6-99ef-4184-ac6a-48b2133235d8", "value": "A ship that is built and primarily intended for war."}
{"id": "edbcc705-c181-4cc5-a520-aa260a92ff76", "value": "A vessel (often small obsolete cruisers or pleasure steamers) equipped with batteries of anti aircraft guns as its main armament."}
{"id": "8cc1fc15-2175-4054-b4f0-aa64785ecc4c", "value": "A capital warship lightly armoured but with the same gun armament and stem turbine propulsion as a DREADNOUGHT BATTLESHIP."}

{"id": "24833e13-2301-4c5a-a46b-758f805f37dc", "value": "A small warship powered by petrol or diesel engines and armed with torpedo tubes and small guns. Used for coastal anti shipping patrols and warfare in coastal waters."}
{"id": "c776b1d2-acdf-4f4a-8ade-621c13e2e52c", "value": "A small stem powered warship with its hull protected by iron plates. Used to bombard targets onshore, especially in the Crimean War."}
{"id": "99a03142-40aa-4d9d-a5d6-6d7786c6bcb9", "value": "A small vessel used to attack other vessels and setting themselves and then the enemy alight."}

{"id": "9a64f5ec-cc95-441d-9a71-31455984f6d9", "value": "Large warship equipped with turret mounted guns. Intended for independent action for trade protection, reconaissance and fire support for amphibious operations."}

{"id": "2ad5a7e5-e5db-4229-ace3-390ecd87d8b0", "value": "A very fast small warship, armed with small calibre guns and torpedoes. Used for attacking enemy vessels, escort duties and anti submarine duties."}

{"id": "d285116c-a856-410e-a1c3-8b2543feb638", "value": "A vessel designed or adapted for the task of keeping shipping lanes and ports free from the threat of naval mines. Use specific type where known. of"}
{"id": "5e539c8f-6199-4150-b3b5-86dce311e871", "value": "A warship used to provide an escort to other warships or merchant ships against attack."}
{"id": "f00dba0e-e364-4368-aae9-f30a6dd10c89", "value": "Inshore craft used for carrying troops and military equipment used either for beach landings or as a ferry. Use specific type where known."}

{"id": "59136385-4c4c-4401-ba1f-138db8c8ba6d", "value": "Transport vessel, usually a hired vessel of mercantile origin, used for the exchange of prisoners-of-war; sometimes, specifically a hospital ship with such prisoners."}
{"id": "4bf2ed5a-2acd-4d7a-99e5-e8c0c36ce933", "value": "A craft used for the transportation of cargoes. Use specific type where known."}
{"id": "4b7acc7c-a4f0-4666-b964-0aad0341a898", "value": "Specially designed/fitted carriers of crew and/or supplies to offshore oil platforms."}

{"id": "939d44bb-6acf-47f4-bf63-d1ad5f29ce5c", "value": "Transport vessel hired for the enforced removal of convicts to penal colonies abroad(e.g. Virginia, Australia), or for their return to Britain."}
{"id": "cb3a772c-0644-4bff-92b4-c0f098db89ea", "value": "A vessel used for transporting passengers or goods."}
{"id": "9724a72c-1ed2-4360-a58a-2ad26eb97fee", "value": "A small vessel used to carry fresh water to ships at anchor or in harbour."}
{"id": "7f4ce0c9-94ba-40f4-9606-79a5ecfec10d", "value": "A craft on which is a machine for the loading and unloading of grain to and from a warehouse."}
{"id": "3e8d1869-7849-46eb-ab83-23075617d9c4", "value": "Unpowered flat bottomed vessel, used for carrying cargo from ship to shore or as a working platform."}
{"id": "e8cea596-9f49-4827-8be0-a94b15fc627b", "value": "A vessel used for the laying and removal of buoys and other navigational markers."}
{"id": "5968fa66-f1f6-4ca8-8599-19cfed7ed91f", "value": "A vessel used to put down and pick up moorings on the sea bed for large vessels."}
{"id": "edda5a5c-add5-4e69-aa23-f8f1f1f4254e", "value": "A relatively small and heavily built vessel equipped with large engines. Used for towing ships at sea or manouevring them in tight spaces."}
{"id": "a07b1009-ef78-407e-9697-cdc1188f27ce", "value": "Craft used to maintain, supply or assist larger vessels whilst in harbour."}
{"id": "ef14413b-3235-4fc6-9809-0c86b46f113e", "value": "A ship used for laying cables (often telephone cables) along the sea bed."}
{"id": "cd0c2dd1-7c5a-4d90-a600-2e567629a131", "value": "A single decked cargo vessel carrying the majority of its cargo on deck."}
{"id": "e7f0b187-890e-4fe9-a1ae-222ade2959e1", "value": "A buoy with a compartment into which shipwrecked mariners could climb to await rescue."}

{"id": "8c865925-a957-41fc-b697-48127ef27268", "value": "A vessel used to carry essential supplies, such as food and armaments, to naval ships in order to keep them replenished whilst on patrol. Use more specific term."}
{"id": "cd80a438-b356-4901-a3db-e5accb21ea01", "value": "A vessel used for carrying mines between warships and supply depots."}
{"id": "9219e57a-d523-4744-a595-5e223d8c16e3", "value": "A vessel used as a platform for flying a barrage balloon from."}
{"id": "2a78a76e-41c4-4cdd-b1e9-566b99cc406c", "value": "A small, fast boat used for carrying orders between sailing vessels."}
{"id": "63f13f1f-344e-486d-828d-2cfc113261bc", "value": "A ship in government use, used to carry naval or military stores."}

{"id": "58848a99-7354-4932-9abe-0e8458de566d", "value": "A small vessel attached to a larger vessel (usually a warship) for general harbour duties such as taking crewmen ashore or fetching supplies."}
{"id": "16346f9f-7b48-4f0b-a2df-8c2b6e3270a4", "value": "A vessel containing equipment for reducing the magnetic structure of a ship's hull making it immune to magnetic mines."}
{"id": "3d07b82f-aedd-4d35-b316-079a6b3f3d9b", "value": "A vessel for policing fishing grounds and fishing vessels."}

{"id": "1de72eee-e8cc-47ff-b059-bea1539d4680", "value": "The name given by the Allies during the Second World War to the German motor torpedo boat. E Boats carried two torpedo tubes and anti aircraft guns. They had a maximum speed of 39 knots and were considered superior to their Allied counterparts."}
{"id": "05915927-095a-469b-8222-094dd681c024", "value": "17th/18th century lightly armed privateer, usually either a 'Dunkirker' or Dutch."}
{"id": "c803603d-6512-44d5-89d1-e0eb17ba5557", "value": "A vessel equipped with water tanks and pumps for fighting fires at sea or on the shore line."}

{"id": "67f97021-1e49-429d-8b80-267c801c6acb", "value": "A type of clinker built wooden boat or ship held together with tendons of flexible wood such as roots and willow branches. Sewn boat construction techniques were used in many parts of the world prior to the development of metal fasteners."}

{"id": "81cca1fd-c4f3-4ee9-819a-ee01f1dbf76a", "value": "Privateer operating under government licence to act against enemy merchant shipping. The term is closely associated with North African privateers which operated off the Barbary coast prior to the mid-1800's."}
{"id": "f3801458-d173-4f77-af56-e9e74d67bb58", "value": "A small sailing vessel armed with guns."}
